Winstone Chiseremi @Wchiseremi Moi Teaching and Referral Hospital (MTRH) in Eldoret has sued an insurance company over breach of contract. In 2016, the hospital management entered into a contract with Alexander Forbes Health Care Limited to provide  medical services cover at a cost of Sh20 million. The hospital claims after making the payment, the insurer rebranded to Afrocentric Health Solution and relocated. MTRH lawyer Karen Chesoo told Justice Hellen Omondi the new developments have made it difficult for the hospital to recover the funds. The lawyer made an application to serve the insurance firm an order to appear before court over the matter. Omondi granted them the request that should be done in two days.